(n=6). Body yellow, cover with numerous long and pointed setae, dark brown dorsal cross-bars on abdominal tergites in life (

).

Mounted specimens: Body elongated (
), 2.88–3.21 mm long, 2.18–2.71 times as long as its width. Dorsum of head and thorax, antennal segments I-II, distal 1/3 of antennal segments III , antennal segments IV-VI, coxae, distal 2/3 of hind femora, tibiae and siphunculi dark brown; basal 2/3 of antennal segments III , apex of ultimate rostral segment, wing veins, basal 1/3 of femora, second tarsal segments brown; cauda and remaining parts of body slightly paler. Dorsal head and thorax sclerotized, abdominal tergites cover with large fused spinal sclerites and oval marginal sclerites, pleural sclerites small and irregular placed (
